A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending Larry Pellegrini; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, Larry Pellegrini has dedicated over 30 years to championing progressive causes
3 and advocating for LGBTQ equality at the Georgia State Capitol; and
4 WHEREAS, he began his journey in advocacy through his volunteer work with Southern
5 Voice and made history as the first openly gay lobbyist at the Georgia State Capitol,
6 advocating for LGBTQ rights at a time when such efforts faced significant opposition and
7 focusing his early work on sodomy law reform; and
8 WHEREAS, Larry Pellegrini participated in the Cracker Barrel campaign, a landmark protest
9 movement that directly challenged employment discrimination against LGBTQ individuals
10 and influenced broader discussions on domestic partnerships and equality; and
11 WHEREAS, he has further served as the executive director of the Georgia Rural Urban
12 Summit, which connects rural and urban progressives, as well as a member of the board of
13 directors for the Georgia Stonewall Democrats; and
