14 WHEREAS, throughout his career, Larry Pellegrini has demonstrated a steadfast
15 commitment to uniting diverse groups in the pursuit of justice, fairness, and equality,
16 working to combat discriminatory legislation and protect fundamental rights; and
17 WHEREAS, he remains a respected leader in Georgia's progressive movement, inspiring a
18 new generation of activists to continue the fight for hate crime protections,
19 non-discrimination policies, and other critical legislative advancements; and
20 WHEREAS, his exemplary efforts and unwavering dedication to advocacy have left an
21 enduring mark on Georgia's political landscape and the broader fight for equality, making
22 it abundantly fitting and proper that he be appropriately honored.
23 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE that the members of this body
24 recognize and commend Larry Pellegrini for his remarkable contributions to progressive
25 advocacy and LGBTQ rights in Georgia and extend best wishes for future health and
26 happiness.
27 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Secretary of the Senate is authorized and directed
28 to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to Larry Pellegrini.
